# Data Layer

> For detailed examples, see [README.md - Mappers](../../README.md#mappers) and [README.md - Error Handling](../../README.md#error-handling).

## Service Layer

- **Must** use services (not repositories) as the abstraction layer
- **Must** define an abstract interface in `domain/service/` (e.g. `abstract interface class OrdersService`)
- **Must** implement in `data/service/` (e.g. `OrdersServiceImpl`)
- **Must** register with `@LazySingleton(as: OrdersService)` or `@Singleton(as: OrdersService)`
- Older modules use `abstract class`; new modules **should** use `abstract interface class`

## DataSource Layer (Retrofit)

- **Must** use Retrofit `@RestApi()` abstract classes for API calls in `data/data_source/`
- **Must** use `factory Xxx(Dio dio)` constructor
- ServiceImpl calls data source, maps DTOs → domain models, handles errors with Either

```dart
@RestApi()
abstract class OrdersDataSource {
  factory OrdersDataSource(Dio dio) = _OrdersDataSource;

  @GET('/orders')
  Future<OrdersResponseDto> getOrders();
}
```

## Mappers

- **Must** use extensions on DTO classes (e.g. `extension UserDtoMapper on UserDto`)
- **Should** name method `toDomain()`
- **Must** handle all field mappings and transformations

## DTOs & JSON Serialization

- **Must** use `@JsonSerializable(createToJson: false)` for read-only DTOs
- **Must not** use `@JsonKey` when JSON key matches field name
- **Must** use `@JsonKey(name: ...)` only when names differ (e.g. snake_case → camelCase)

```dart
@JsonSerializable(createToJson: false)
class UserDto {
  @JsonKey(name: 'user_id')
  final int userId;
  final String userName;
}
```

## Polymorphic DTOs

When a JSON `type` (or similar discriminator) field determines which DTO subclass to instantiate:

- **Must** handle unknown `type` values gracefully — return an unknown/null sentinel, **never** throw
- **Must** filter out unknown items during `toDomain()` mapping — return nullable, filter with `whereType`
- **Must** use `is` pattern matching (not `runtimeType`) for type dispatch in mapper extensions
- **Must** name DTO and domain model classes to match API terminology (e.g. if API sends `"type": "text"`, use `TextOptionDto`, not `OtherOptionDto`)

```dart
// ✅ Good — unknown types handled gracefully, is-pattern dispatch
abstract class ItemDto {
  const ItemDto();

  factory ItemDto.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
    return switch (json['type'] as String?) {
      'typeA' => TypeAItemDto.fromJson(json),
      'typeB' => TypeBItemDto.fromJson(json),
      _ => const _UnknownItemDto(),
    };
  }
}

class _UnknownItemDto extends ItemDto {
  const _UnknownItemDto();
}

extension ItemDtoMapper on ItemDto {
  DomainModel? toDomain() => switch (this) {
    final TypeAItemDto dto => dto.toDomain(),
    final TypeBItemDto dto => dto.toDomain(),
    _ => null,
  };
}

// List mapper filters out unknowns
extension ItemListDtoMapper on ItemListDto {
  List<DomainModel> toDomain() => items
      .map((ItemDto item) => item.toDomain())
      .whereType<DomainModel>()
      .toList(growable: false);
}
```

```dart
// ❌ Bad — throws on unknown type, uses runtimeType
factory ItemDto.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) {
  return switch (json['type'] as String?) {
    'typeA' => TypeAItemDto.fromJson(json),
    _ => throw UnsupportedError('Unknown type'),
  };
}

extension ItemDtoMapper on ItemDto {
  DomainModel toDomain() => switch (runtimeType) {
    const (TypeAItemDto) => (this as TypeAItemDto).toDomain(),
    _ => throw UnsupportedError('Unknown'),
  };
}
```

## API Enums

- **Must** use enums with `apiCode` field and `fromCode(String? code)` static parser
- Parser must: handle null/empty → default, normalize input, use `firstWhere` with `orElse`
- Domain and UI use the enum, not raw strings

```dart
enum OrderDetailsPaymentMethod {
  verifoneHosted('verifone_hosted'),
  paypalExpress('paypal_express'),
  unknown('unknown');

  const OrderDetailsPaymentMethod(this.apiCode);
  final String apiCode;

  static OrderDetailsPaymentMethod fromCode(String? code) {
    if (code == null || code.isEmpty) return OrderDetailsPaymentMethod.unknown;
    final String normalized = code.trim().toLowerCase();
    return OrderDetailsPaymentMethod.values.firstWhere(
      (OrderDetailsPaymentMethod method) => method.apiCode == normalized,
      orElse: () => OrderDetailsPaymentMethod.unknown,
    );
  }
}
```

## Error Handling

### Either Pattern
- **Must** return `Either<ErrorType, SuccessType>` from service methods
- `Success<L, R>` for success, `Failure<L, R>` for failure
- Use `.fold()` in presentation layer to handle both cases

Key methods: `fold()`, `map()`, `flatMap()`, `getOrElse()`, `isSuccess()`, `isFailure()`

### Data Layer
- **Must** catch only expected exceptions
- Let unexpected exceptions bubble up automatically

```dart
try {
  return Success<ErrorType, DataType>(data);
} on ExpectedException catch (e, st) {
  return Failure<ErrorType, DataType>(SpecificError(message: e.message));
}
```

### Error Types
- **Must** inherit from `GenericError`
- **Should** use sealed classes for error hierarchies

